OL,3,CFrom Birmingham to a global empire:
OL,4,CTimeline shows Cadbury's sweet success
OL,6,FTimeline of how Cadbury become a
OL,7,Fglobal empire:
OL,9,F1824: John Cadbury opened the first
OL,10,FCadbury shop at 93 Bull Street in
OL,11,FBirmingham, complete with plate glass
OL,12,Fwindows with mahogany frames, which he
OL,13,Fwas said to have cleaned every day. He
OL,14,Fsold cocoa and drinking chocolate,
OL,15,Fwhich he prepared himself using a
OL,16,Fpestle and mortar, amongst other
OL,17,Fthings.
OL,19,F1866: Launch of cocoa essence, marking
OL,20,Fa major turning point for Cadbury.
